🔊 Audio Synthesis Engine (game/sound-manager.js)
[NEW] 
sound-manager.js
We will write a comprehensive sound synthesizer and playback manager using standard Web Audio API.

Audio Synthesis Engine:
Lobby BGM: A soothing, slow ambient chord progression (Am - F - C - G) synthesized using lowpass-filtered sine waves and a delay/echo feedback loop.
In-game BGM: An energetic synthwave bassline and running pulse pattern.
Gameover BGM: A melancholic, slowing, decaying minor-key arpeggio.
18 Sound Effects: High-quality procedural synthesis with customizable parameters:
ball-launch: Quick pitch sweep downwards (sine, 50ms)
ball-wall: Fast high-pitch click (triangle, 30ms)
ball-hit: Juicy impact pop (square, 80ms)
ball-collect: Rising bubble sound (sine, 60ms)
ball-all-collected: Double chime (triangle, 200ms)
enemy-kill: Deep filtered noise explosion (noise + sine, 150ms)
enemy-spawn: Low sweep "wub" (sine, 250ms)
enemy-descend: Heavy mechanical thud (square, 300ms)
enemy-deadline: Urgent warning buzz
ui-click, ui-hover: Crisp clicks and subtle tick sounds
skill-popup, skill-power, skill-multi, skill-speed: Specialized magical/digital power-up sound sweeps
Audio Controllers:
Volume control (Mute/Unmute, Master volume).
Auto-starts audio context on user interaction (resolving modern browser blocking).
Support for checking if actual local audio files exist in assets/ and auto-playing them instead of synthetic sound.
